details.text: Andrew Thomas Carroll (born 6 January 1989) is an English professional footballer who plays as a striker for West Bromwich Albion.

details.name: Swiss Football Association
details.text: The Swiss Football Association (German: Schweizerischer Fussballverband, French: Association Suisse de Football, Italian: Associazione Svizzera di Football/Calcio, Romansh: Associaziun Svizra da Ballape) is the governing body of football in Switzerland.

details.name: Brazilian Football Confederation
details.text: The Brazilian Football Confederation (Portuguese: Confederação Brasileira de Futebol; CBF) is the governing body of football in Brazil.

details.name: Turkish Football Federation
details.text: The Turkish Football Federation (Turkish: Türkiye Futbol Federasyonu; TFF) is the governing body of association football in Turkey.

details.name: UEFA European Under-21 Championship
details.text: The UEFA European Under-21 Championship, the UEFA Under-21 Championship or simply the Euro Under-21, is a biennial football competition contested by the European men's under-21 national teams of the UEFA member associations.

details.name: Midfielder
details.text: A midfielder is an association football position.

details.name: Austrian Football Association
details.text: The Austrian Football Association (German: Österreichischer Fußball-Bund; ÖFB) is the governing body of football in Austria.

details.name: Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.
details.text: Wolverhampton Wanderers Football Club ( (listen)), commonly known as Wolves, is a professional association football club based in Wolverhampton, England.

details.name: Filbert Street
details.text: Filbert Street was a football stadium in Leicester, England, which served as the home of Leicester City F.C.

details.name: FC Barcelona
details.text: Futbol Club Barcelona (Catalan pronunciation: [fubˈbɔl ˈklub bəɾsəˈlonə] (listen)), commonly referred to as Barcelona and colloquially known as Barça ([ˈbaɾsə]), is a professional football club based in Barcelona, Spain, that competes in La Liga, the top flight of Spanish football.

details.name: The Football Association
details.text: The Football Association (also known as The FA) is the governing body of association football in England and the Crown dependencies of Jersey, Guernsey and the Isle of Man.

details.name: EFL Cup
details.text: The EFL Cup (referred to historically, and colloquially, as the League Cup), currently known as the Carabao Cup for sponsorship reasons, is an annual knockout football competition and major trophy in men's domestic English football.

details.name: County cup
details.text: The county football associations are the local governing bodies of association football in England and the Crown dependencies.

details.name: Polish Football Association
details.text: The Polish Football Association (Polish: Polski Związek Piłki Nożnej; PZPN) is the governing body of association football in Poland.

details.name: Irish Football Association
details.text: The Irish Football Association (IFA) is the governing body for association football in Northern Ireland.

details.name: Wembley Stadium
details.text: Wembley Stadium (branded as Wembley Stadium connected by EE for sponsorship reasons) is a football stadium in Wembley, London.

details.name: UEFA Cup Winners' Cup
details.text: The UEFA Cup Winners' Cup  was a European football club competition contested annually by the winners of domestic cup competitions.

details.name: Professional Footballers' Association
details.text: The Professional Footballers' Association (PFA) is the trade union for professional association footballers in England and Wales.

details.name: UEFA competitions
details.text: UEFA competitions (French: competitions de l'UEFA), referred improperly by the mass media as European football, are the set of tournaments organised by the Union of European Football Associations (UEFA), generally in professional and amateur association football and futsal.

details.name: Old Trafford
details.text: Old Trafford () is a football stadium in Old Trafford, Greater Manchester, England, and the home of Manchester United.

details.name: Kenny Sansom
details.text: Kenneth Graham Sansom (born 26 September 1958) is a former professional footballer who played as a defender.

details.name: UEFA European Championship
details.text: The UEFA European Football Championship, less formally the European Championship and informally the Euros, is the primary association football tournament organized by the Union of European Football Associations (UEFA).

details.name: Football Association of Ireland
details.text: The Football Association of Ireland (FAI; Irish: Cumann Peile na hÉireann) is the governing body for association football in the Republic of Ireland.

details.name: Ian Wright
details.text: Ian Edward Wright  (born 3 November 1963) is an English former professional footballer, and television and radio personality.

details.name: London
details.text: London is the capital and largest city of England and the United Kingdom.

details.name: Irish Cup
details.text: The Irish Football Association Challenge Cup, commonly referred to as the Irish Cup (currently known as the Samuel Gelston's Whiskey Irish Cup for sponsorship purposes) is the primary football knock-out cup competition in Northern Ireland.

details.name: Asian Football Confederation
details.text: The Asian Football Confederation is a governing body of association football, beach soccer, and futsal in some countries/territories in Asia and Oceania.

details.name: The Hawthorns
details.text: The Hawthorns is an all-seater football stadium in West Bromwich, West Midlands, England, with a capacity of 26,688.

details.name: Craven Cottage
details.text: Craven Cottage is a football ground in Fulham, West London, England, which has been the home of Fulham F.C.

details.name: UEFA
details.text: The Union of European Football Associations (UEFA  yoo-AY-fə; French: Union des associations européennes de football; German: Union der europäischen Fußballverbände) Polish: Unia Europejskich Związków Piłkarskich is the administrative body for football, futsal and beach soccer in Europe, as well as Armenia, Israel and the Asian parts of some transcontinental countries.

details.name: Stan Cullis
details.text: Stanley Cullis (25 October 1916 – 28 February 2001) was an English professional footballer and manager, primarily for Wolverhampton Wanderers.

details.name: FIFA
details.text: FIFA  ( French: Fédération Internationale de Football Association; English: International Federation of Association Football; Spanish: Federación Internacional de Fútbol Asociación; German: Internationaler Verband des Association-Fußball; Russian: Международная федерация футбола; Arabic: الاتحاد الدولي لكرة القدم) is a non-profit organization that describes itself as an international governing body of association football, futsal and beach soccer.

details.name: England
details.text: England is a country that is part of the United Kingdom.

details.name: Scotland
details.text: Scotland (Scots: Scotland, Scottish Gaelic: Alba [ˈal̪ˠapə] (listen)) is a country that is part of the United Kingdom.

details.name: Wales
details.text: Wales (Welsh: Cymru [ˈkəm.rɨ] (listen)) is a country that is part of the United Kingdom.

details.name: Portuguese name
details.text: A Portuguese name is typically composed of one or two given names, and a number of family names (rarely one, often two or three, sometimes more).
